<div style="background-color: #58585858; border-left: 8px solid #FFFFFF; border-right: 8px solid #FFFFFF; padding: 10px 12px; margin: 0.1em;">Have you ever wondered, why is technology of the past seemingly anomalous, either some magical clock or some neon sign that hypnotises you, if it is made in the past and considered to be "old" technology, it gains powers? I noticed these patterns and propose a theory: as humanity advances, the Backrooms collects these forgotten remains and infuses it with itself so these machines also become bizarre in nature. So far, with all this evidence, I am most likely right.</div><br><br>

Phenomenon 6 or Technological Compatibility is that affects <u>most</u> outdated technology within the Backrooms. It is responsible for ensuring machinery or inventions made will remain in use even if they are no longer the best invention of the current era. Any piece of technology that is deemed as outdated will receive a Backrooms exclusive phenomenon attached to them which will ensure that any device used has a purpose and is not discarded.

Ropes were given [[Phenomenon 25|prophetic abilities]], doors may act as portals to other levels, radios can [[Phenomenon 28|speak to the dead]], electrical generators found in [[Level 3]] supply power to the Backrooms, even loud alarms and sirens found in levels are often found in levels with large [[Entity List|entity]] populations which can distract creatures or warn wanderers they entered a dangerous level.

While Phenomenon 6 is helpful, when not properly used these blessings can cause much harm such as creating strobing affects intended to stun entities, old pipes that heat up to be used as a furnace but instead burn wanderers alive and even clockwork machines being mishandled and ending up crushing wanderers to death. The reason why [[M.E.G.|we]] are certain that Phenomenon 6 is in our interests is due to entities and even books found within the Backrooms that refer to an anomalous blessing given to abandoned tools which encourage use.

Of course, using old technology is dangerous as we need modern weapons to deal with ever adapting entities and threats, so this can be used as a counter argument revealing that the Backrooms is trying to force primitive nature onto humans to discourage safety in technological advancements. Some even point out how certain groups like [[Groups|Marauders]] are technologically more advanced than humans yet current technology doesn't appear to have anomalous assistance. Some suggest that [[Phenomenon 2|BACK-NET]] is humanity's next technology upgrade until we are as advanced.

It is theorised that technology based entities are a hostile form of Phenomenon 6 yet this remains unknown, some entities claim that creatures like [[The Mustang]] always existed even before technology claimed to be made by humans was invented, in fact brands found in the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] experienced time anomalies where they existed before they were made. For example, various Pepsi and Coca-cola vending machines are found in levels way before even soda ingredients were discovered.

Phenomenon 6 continues to fascinate, change and adapt every year and we should do the same.

